WEBVTT

NOTE
Q2 Planning Sync - March 26, 2026
Participants: Ankit (Engineering Lead), Priya (HR Manager), Mrinal (Product Manager)

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
<v Ankit>Good morning everyone. Let's kick off our Q2 planning sync.

00:00:05.500 --> 00:00:12.000
<v Ankit>First item on the agenda - we need to update the PROJ-456 ticket with the new deadline for the API migration.

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:18.500
<v Ankit>I'll take ownership of that. Let's push the deadline to April 10th to give us more buffer time.

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:24.000
<v Priya>Sounds good. Moving on to hiring - we have an urgent need for a backend engineer.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:32.000
<v Priya>I'll be the hiring manager for this role. We need someone to start by March 28th if possible.

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:39.000
<v Priya>The position is for a Senior Backend Engineer in the Platform Engineering department.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:46.000
<v Mrinal>Great. On the infrastructure side, we need to address our AWS spend limit.

00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:54.000
<v Mrinal>Let's raise the AWS spend limit by 40k for the quarter. I'll own this procurement request.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:01:01.000
<v Mrinal>We need this approved by end of day today, March 26th, to avoid service disruptions.

00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:08.000
<v Mrinal>Also, I need to create a new Jira ticket for the mobile app performance optimization project.

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:16.000
<v Mrinal>This should go in the MOBILE project, high priority, and I'll assign it to myself. Target completion by April 1st.

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:23.000
<v Ankit>Perfect. One more thing - we should probably review our pricing model at some point.

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
<v Ankit>Not sure when exactly, but it's something to keep in mind.

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:33.000
<v Priya>Agreed. Let's revisit that in a future meeting.

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:38.000
<v Mrinal>Alright, I think that covers everything. Thanks everyone.

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:42.000
<v Ankit>Thanks all. Have a great day.
